$ /etc/tdnf/tdnf.conf

`/etc/tdnf/tdnf.conf` is the configuration file of the → Linux/package-managers/TDNF[TNDF package manager].

This files stores information on how TDNF should handle caching and other local functions
and contains a pointer to the repo configuration directory. Because of its YUM heritage, the default is to point to `→ Linux/fhs/etc/yum_repos_d` which contains the list of repo configuration files.
